673 A.2d 705 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. James Edward BOSWELL. Misc. (Subtitle BV) No. 2,

Sept. Term, 1996.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. March 21, 1996.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Consent to Disbarment from the practice of law filed by James Edward Boswell, in accordance with Maryland Rule BV12d2, and the written recommendation of Bar Counsel, it is this 21st day of March, 1996

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that James Edward Boswell be, and he is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further

ORDERED that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of James Edward Boswell from the register of attorneys, and, pursuant to Maryland Rule BV13, shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Clients’ Security Trust Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
